      "date": "2014-02-22 14:43:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nJames: size_t is implementation defined; it's guaranteed to be the type of a sizeof expression. Therefore we cannot put size_t in struct which go on the wire. But IIRC there are places where obd_count is used but doesn't go on the wire. There are also tons of places where int or unsigned int is used but we should be using size_t or ssize_t.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
